  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Community Initiatives for Risk and Disaster Management</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Risk reduction is achieved through environmental education and training, formulation of disaster risk reduction community groups, research and evaluation of capacities and vulnerabilities, and the design and implementation of local development plans. Simulation sessions will be held to facilitate training, education and sustainability effects. Rapid response teams will be established by committee and churches to aid in emergency or disaster response as well as material distribution.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Integrated Community Initiatives for Risk and Disaster Management project aims to reduce the impact of natural disasters for 52,197 people living in Southeast communities of Haiti (Jacmel, Cayes-Jacmel, Marigot, Grand-Gosier and L&#xE9;ogane). World Concern aims to improve the living conditions and increase and strengthen the resilience of communities by the Climate Change Adaptation and Management Risk and Disaster models which will address the reasons and factors that generate risks and thereby reduce the impact of disasters. World Concern will work with each community to develop action plans by systematic applications.</narrative>
  </description>
